    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-17T14:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-17T14:36:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24359: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-17T13:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1920—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>331. <hi rend="italic">El Democrata</hi> today publishes the statement that the
                    Government of Venezuela has decided that Constitutional order has not been
                    interrupted in Mexico and consequently has recognized the Mexican Government of
                    Substitute President de la Huerta. The Foreign Office has advised me informally
                    that this statement is correct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
